records.addlTxt:
Defendant Patrick J McVey in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph Edward Schubert.   Ted Szczupakiewicz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court makes statements, defendant wishes to move forward with the plea and does not wish to have a PSI done.  State withdraws request for a PSI.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Schubert makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  

The Court Orders the Following:  Count #5

Sentence of:

39 months Imprisonment (Credit - 230 days)

15 months of Initial Confinement

24 months of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision

Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

No contact with co-actors except for legal proceedings as it pertains to his wife.

AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;

Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;

No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;

Sign Medical Release for Agent;

Seek employment;

COSTS:  $268.00 Bail to be applied

DNA Surcharge: $250.00 Bail to be applied, remainder to be paid as a condition of extended supervision

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program

Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
